{
  "answer": "**The Yama Smṛti (unknown author), Chapter 1,** declares this in verses YSS 1.12–13.[^1]\n\nThe paired verses are quoted verbatim below:\n\n> For each single sin that is committed, the wise know a penance; / but when all sins converge, no penance is known. // YSS_1.12 //[^2]\n\n> When all sins converge, taking up the skull-bowl is prescribed; / that Kāpālika vow is considered its ultimate penance by the wise. // YSS_1.13 //[^3]\n\n[^1]: Yama Smṛti, [Chapter 1](/works/unknown-yama-smrti-552f8d/01/translation/).\n[^2]: Yama Smṛti, [paragraph](/works/unknown-yama-smrti-552f8d/01/translation/#p-423161).\n[^3]: Yama Smṛti, [paragraph](/works/unknown-yama-smrti-552f8d/01/translation/#p-22899e).",
